Could have been a doctor's office, bank, restaurant.

117
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,433
我记得最后一次用它
The last time I remember using it

118
00:06:04,435 --> 00:06:06,185
是昨天早上为我女儿
was when I signed a permission slip

119
00:06:06,187 --> 00:06:08,187
签一份同意书的时候
for my daughter yesterday morning.

120
00:06:08,189 --> 00:06:10,356
在那之后 我一定是把笔放进了口袋
And I must have put the pen in my pocket after that,

121
00:06:10,358 --> 00:06:13,359
但我不知道它在录音
but I had no idea it was recording me.

122
00:06:13,361 --> 00:06:15,811
好的
Okay.

123
00:06:16,696 --> 00:06:18,447
你相信我的话
You believe that?

124
00:06:18,449 --> 00:06:20,533
-是的 -为什么
- Yes. - Why?

125
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:27,856
因为尊重
Respect.

126
00:06:27,858 --> 00:06:29,524
对你 以及这个部门的尊重
For you and the office.

127
00:06:29,526 --> 00:06:31,693
除非有确凿证据
And until there's evidence to the contrary,

128
00:06:31,695 --> 00:06:34,129
否则就假定你是无辜的 部长女士 
you'll get the benefit of the doubt, Madam Secretary.

129
00:06:34,131 --> 00:06:36,198
谢谢你 Gibbs探员
Thank you, Agent Gibbs.

130
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:39,051
现在要做的事 是在信息泄露之前追查
Job now is finding who's responsible

131
00:06:39,053 --> 00:06:40,636
谁对这起窃听事件负有责任
before anything leaks.

132
00:06:40,638 --> 00:06:43,672
我昨天在秘密场所参加了
I had classified briefings

133
00:06:43,674 --> 00:06:46,725
国防部的三场机密情报会议
at three D.O.D. off-site locations yesterday,

134
00:06:46,727 --> 00:06:49,061
而且我们所探讨的部署策略
and we talked enough deployment strategy

135
00:06:49,063 --> 00:06:50,879
能够对海军和海军陆战队
to cause serious security problems

136
00:06:50,881 --> 00:06:53,065
造成严重的安全问题
for the sailors and Marines I work for.

137
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:56,986
请你理解 他们的安危是我唯一关心的 Gibbs探员
Understand, they are my only concern in this, Agent Gibbs.

138
00:07:03,494 --> 00:07:06,111
Abby已经拿了那只窃听笔 老大 
Abby's got the spy pen, boss.

139
00:07:06,113 --> 00:07:09,564
根据电池容量以及剩余电量分析
Based on the battery size and the length of the charge left,

140
00:07:09,566 --> 00:07:12,418
我们认为它录音了将近30个小时左右
we think it's been recording for about 30 hours or so.

141
00:07:14,371 --> 00:07:15,621
我们能追踪到是谁在窃听吗
Can we track who's listening?

142
00:07:15,623 --> 00:07:16,622
这不是现场直播
It's not a live feed.

143
00:07:16,624 --> 00:07:17,957
窃听器只存储信息
The bug stores the data internally,

144
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:19,425
这意味着安置窃听器的人
which means whoever planted it

145
00:07:19,427 --> 00:07:20,876
必须得下载这些信息
has to download the info.

146
00:07:20,878 --> 00:07:23,412
我们必须假设他们已经这么做了
Which we have to assume they've already done.

147
00:07:23,414 --> 00:07:25,798
好吧 我会警示五角大楼
All right, I will alert the Pentagon that my meetings

148
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,882
昨天的会议内容被泄露了
yesterday were compromised.

149
00:07:26,884 --> 00:07:28,934
我们应该和NSA共同处理这个问题
【注：NSA 美国国家安全局】
And we should bring in the NSA.

150
00:07:28,936 --> 00:07:31,220
我刚刚提出了这个请求
I just put in a request for info.

151
00:07:31,222 --> 00:07:34,089
让他们时刻警惕有关出卖美国情报的问题
They got ears open for the sale of U.S. intel.

152
00:07:34,091 --> 00:07:35,140
我们尽力不要让事情发展到那个地步
Let's make sure it doesn't get that far.

153
00:07:35,142 --> 00:07:36,425
我跟着你做 老大
You zig, I zag, boss.

154
00:07:36,427 --> 00:07:38,277
我在和NSA通电话时
While I was on the horn with NSA,

155
00:07:38,279 --> 00:07:40,112
调出了一份威胁分析报告
I pulled a threat analysis report.

156
00:07:40,114 --> 00:07:42,531
他们在十分钟内就做了这份报告吗
They put this together in the last ten minutes?

157
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:44,433
不 这报告在两年前就完成了
No. The paper's two years old.

158
00:07:44,435 --> 00:07:46,368
但是它准确地预言了我们这次的泄露事件
But it predicts our breach exactly.

159
00:07:46,370 --> 00:07:48,537
"秘密录音装置"
"Clandestine recording device,

160
00:07:48,539 --> 00:07:50,939
"高级别的政府官员"
"high-level government official,

161
00:07:50,941 --> 00:07:52,875
"一件日常用品
"an everyday item

162
00:07:52,877 --> 00:07:55,077
例如一支钢笔"
such as an ink pen."

163
00:07:56,379 --> 00:07:57,663
巧合吗
Coincidence?

164
00:07:57,665 --> 00:08:01,450
我们得和写这份报告的人谈一谈
We need to talk to the person who wrote this paper.

165
00:08:10,226 --> 00:08:12,594
我还以为要经过全面细致地搜身才能进来这里呢
I thought we were gonna get a cavity search coming in here.

166
00:08:12,596 --> 00:08:14,930
真有趣
Interesting.

167
00:08:14,932 --> 00:08:16,098
嗯
Hmm.

168
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,600
哇 看那里
Whoa, look at that.

169
00:08:18,602 --> 00:08:22,521
我们最好别告诉McGee 这里有《星际迷航》游戏里的椅子
We better not tell McGee about the <i>Star Trek</i> video game chairs.

170
00:08:22,523 --> 00:08:25,307
他会疯了的
It'll just irritate him.

171
00:08:25,309 --> 00:08:27,776
这儿就像是苹果直营店
It's like an Apple Store.

172
00:08:27,778 --> 00:08:29,445
你们一定是NCIS吧
You must be NCIS.

