在海军部长的身上放置窃听器
on the Secretary of the Navy!

407
00:17:59,303 --> 00:18:01,153
你胆大包天 竟敢指控我犯叛国罪
You got stones accusing me of treason.

408
00:18:01,155 --> 00:18:02,621
互相责怪是没有用的
There's no sense pointing fingers.

409
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:04,022
别假装是个爱国者了 Ward
Quit playing the patriot, Ward.

410
00:18:04,024 --> 00:18:07,726
我是一个爱国者 我的公司为这个军队服务了四代人
I am a patriot. My company's been serving this military for four generations.

412
00:18:07,728 --> 00:18:10,395
我们可不是什么发战争财的公司
We're not some startup war profiteer.

413
00:18:10,397 --> 00:18:11,880
够了
That's enough.

414
00:18:11,882 --> 00:18:13,565
我知道你们都担心
I understand you're concerned

415
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:14,683
公司机密被泄露
about corporate secrets being leaked.

416
00:18:14,685 --> 00:18:16,268
即使没有任何泄露
Even if nothing leaks,

417
00:18:16,270 --> 00:18:18,270
像这样的话传出去也会让我的公司倒闭
word of this would kill me on Wall Street.

418
00:18:18,272 --> 00:18:20,773
我们讨论的是上亿的金钱
We're talking hundreds of millions.

419
00:18:20,775 --> 00:18:22,390
我们正在追踪那个从你员工身上找到的监听器 Marc
We are following up on the device found on your employee, Marc,

420
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:26,061
但你得给我们一点时间来做我们的工作
but give us time to do our jobs.

421
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:27,395
我可以向你们俩保证
I can assure you both

422
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:29,615
我们最好的探员正在日以继夜地工作
that our best agents are working on this around the clock.

423
00:18:29,617 --> 00:18:31,200
对不对 Gibbs探员
Isn't that right, Agent Gibbs?

424
00:18:32,568 --> 00:18:36,121
哦 我确定你刚刚让我们都出局了 长官
Oh, I'm pretty sure you just took us off the clock, ma'am.

425
00:18:38,758 --> 00:18:42,294
先生们 失陪一下
Gentlemen, if you'll excuse me for a moment.

426
00:18:44,130 --> 00:18:46,014
我因为这件事情承受着各方压力
I'm getting hit on all sides with this--

427
00:18:46,016 --> 00:18:47,516
五角大楼 白宫
Pentagon, White House.

428
00:18:47,518 --> 00:18:50,302
人们不需要另一个情报丑闻
【注：指斯诺登的棱镜门】 
Last thing anybody needs is another intel scandal,

429
00:18:50,304 --> 00:18:52,938
而且NSA对这种威胁有所防备
and NSA is prepared for this kind of threat.

430
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:54,273
我们也是 部长女士
So are we, Madam Secretary.

431
00:18:54,275 --> 00:18:56,424
我希望你能继续以往出色的工作 Leon
And I want you to keep up the good work, Leon.

432
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:59,061
我不是把你当成候补 只是在增加更多的人手
I'm not benching you; I'm just adding more players to the game.

433
00:18:59,063 --> 00:19:01,230
术业有专攻 
Different players have different strengths.

434
00:19:01,232 --> 00:19:06,318
是的 而作为总指挥 我要根据我的方法来编排阵容 主任 
Yes, and as head coach, I have the lineup just the way I want it, Director.

436
00:19:08,371 --> 00:19:10,105
尔等明白了吗
Is that understood?

437
00:19:12,942 --> 00:19:14,827
每一个人都在盯着
Everybody's looking

438
00:19:14,829 --> 00:19:17,112
一个没有军事背景的女性海军部长
at a female SECNAV with no military background,

439
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:18,964
疑心这两点
wondering if either one of those things

440
00:19:18,966 --> 00:19:20,549
会不会造成问题
are gonna be a factor.

441
00:19:20,551 --> 00:19:23,618
我希望能够妥善处理此事 让他们瞧瞧
I'd like to answer them by setting this right.

442
00:19:24,754 --> 00:19:28,757
因此 我需要得到所有的帮助
And to do that, I need all the help I can get.

443
00:19:28,759 --> 00:19:30,959
尤其是你们的
Especially yours.

444
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:40,185
哦 天啊
Oh, God.

445
00:19:41,155 --> 00:19:44,239
愚蠢的笔 给我答案吧
Stupid pen, give me answers.

446
00:19:47,527 --> 00:19:49,578
你在那儿站了多久了
How long have you been standing there?

447
00:19:49,580 --> 00:19:51,363
哦 几分钟罢了
Oh, just a few minutes.

448
00:19:51,365 --> 00:19:53,532
-我以为你知道的 -我不知道
- I thought you knew. - No.

449
00:19:53,534 --> 00:19:55,667
但是你跟我说话来着
But you were talking to me.

450
00:19:55,669 --> 00:20:01,590
不 我是在跟我自己 还有一支...笔说话
No, I-I was talking to myself and a... pen.

452
00:20:01,592 --> 00:20:03,842
但是现在起我不会再说了
But now I'm not talking anymore,

453
00:20:03,844 --> 00:20:05,660
谁知道有谁在偷听
cause who knows who's listening?

454
00:20:05,662 --> 00:20:09,164
你觉得谁在偷听
Who do you think's listening?

455
00:20:17,357 --> 00:20:19,841
哦 不...不要相信你听说过的任何事情
Oh, no... don't believe everything you hear.

456
00:20:19,843 --> 00:20:23,678
我们不会随便地监听对话和电话
I mean, we don't randomly listen to conversations and phone calls.

458
00:20:27,150 --> 00:20:28,617
我是认真的
I'm serious.

459
00:20:28,619 --> 00:20:30,518
像你们一样 我们监听也需要法院指令
We need a court order just like you.

460
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:32,871
我们中确实有一些坏家伙
We've had a few bad apples,

461
00:20:32,873 --> 00:20:34,823
但我们是好人
but we're good people

462
00:20:34,825 --> 00:20:37,125
维护法律 作出改变
out to uphold the law and make a difference.

463
00:20:38,044 --> 00:20:40,379
所以你没有监听我的电话
So you haven't bugged my phone?

464
00:20:41,665 --> 00:20:44,716
听着 我可以证明 我来这里只是为了帮忙
Look, I can prove I'm here to help.

465
00:20:44,718 --> 00:20:49,086
关于那个冒牌FBI探员 根据特区法医的描述 我画了这个
I drew this using D.C. examiner's description of our bogus FBI agent,

