Actually, I just checked the offshore account.

530
00:23:47,997 --> 00:23:49,663
那笔勒索费还在
The extortion money's still there.

531
00:23:49,665 --> 00:23:51,565
他没动那一千万美元
He left behind ten million bucks.

532
00:23:51,567 --> 00:23:53,667
-这没有道理 -可能是杀了人之后吓坏了
- doesn't make any sense. - Could've panicked after the shooting.

533
00:23:53,669 --> 00:23:55,503
也许这家伙没有我们想的那么专业
Maybe this guy's not as professional as we thought.

534
00:23:55,505 --> 00:23:59,173
或者 这从一开始就与勒索山姆大叔无关
【注：山姆大叔就是美国政府】
Or maybe it's not about Uncle Sam's money in the first place.

536
00:23:59,175 --> 00:24:03,911
通过诱杀一个联邦探员 Stalin还可以得到什么
What... what else does Stalin get by luring and killing a federal agent?

538
00:24:07,081 --> 00:24:09,016
证明 向另一个买家证明
Authentication. Proof to another buyer

539
00:24:09,018 --> 00:24:10,885
这个情报是真的
that his intel is genuine.

540
00:24:10,887 --> 00:24:12,523
有人愿意支付超过一千万美元
Somebody willing to pay more than ten mil.

541
00:24:12,524 --> 00:24:13,296
所以他利用了我们
So he used us?

542
00:24:13,321 --> 00:24:15,470
这家伙在下棋 而我竟然从来没发现
This guy was playing chess, and I never even saw it.

543
00:24:17,275 --> 00:24:19,760
我知道我要做什么
I know what I have to do.

544
00:24:22,113 --> 00:24:23,480
清零
Reset.

545
00:24:23,482 --> 00:24:26,066
我会重新来一遍
I'll start over.

546
00:24:26,068 --> 00:24:27,651
-Bishop. -这次我能够查出来的
- Bishop. - I'll get it this time.

547
00:24:27,653 --> 00:24:29,620
我只是需要一些时间来清理棋盘
I just need some time to clear the chessboard.

548
00:24:29,622 --> 00:24:31,605
Bishop
Bishop.

549
00:24:31,607 --> 00:24:32,790
休息一下
Take a break.

550
00:24:34,275 --> 00:24:35,609
去买瓶饮料
Go get a soda.

551
00:24:35,611 --> 00:24:39,112
没有时间 而且我没零钱
There's no time, and I have no cash.

552
00:24:44,636 --> 00:24:46,220
拿着
Take it.

553
00:24:49,926 --> 00:24:50,891
是的 Abbs
Yeah, Abbs?

554
00:24:50,893 --> 00:24:52,309
-你可以来我的实验室吗 -可以
- Can you come to my lab? - Yep.

555
00:24:56,381 --> 00:24:58,966
米开朗基罗 莎士比亚 达芬奇 海明威
Michelangelo, Shakespeare, da Vinci, Hemingway.

556
00:24:58,968 --> 00:25:01,268
今天 你可以把我的名字加入他们的行列了 Gibbs
Today, you can count me amongst their ranks, Gibbs.

557
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:03,320
-我每天都这么干的 Abbs -你查到了什么
- I do every day, Abbs. - What do you got?

558
00:25:03,322 --> 00:25:05,522
一个大师级的线索
A masterpiece.

559
00:25:05,524 --> 00:25:07,942
看起来像是一个日期和时间
Well, it looks like a date and time stamp.

560
00:25:07,944 --> 00:25:10,561
有的时候 最伟大的艺术作品往往最简单
Sometimes the greatest works of art are simple.

561
00:25:10,563 --> 00:25:12,980
-你搞定这支笔了 -没 我失败了
- You got into the pen? - No. I failed.

562
00:25:12,982 --> 00:25:15,315
内置的存储芯片加密得实在太好了
The internal memory chip was too well encrypted.

563
00:25:15,317 --> 00:25:16,333
那这是什么 Abbs
Then what is this, Abbs?

564
00:25:16,335 --> 00:25:21,755
这是通过无线传感器登陆这个芯片的最后日期和时间
That is the last day and time the chip was accessedby the Wi-Fi transmitter

566
00:25:22,540 --> 00:25:25,509
啊 就是芯片的发送端
Ah. That the send-y part?

567
00:25:25,511 --> 00:25:27,011
是的
Yes.

568
00:25:27,013 --> 00:25:28,963
所以 我不能告诉你
So, I can't tell you

569
00:25:28,965 --> 00:25:30,848
我们的坏家伙从这支笔里下载了什么
what our bad guy downloaded from the pen,

570
00:25:30,850 --> 00:25:32,833
但是 因为芯片的发送端
but, because of the send-y part,

571
00:25:32,835 --> 00:25:34,351
我可以告诉你他什么时候下载的
I can tell you when he did it.

572
00:25:34,353 --> 00:25:36,470
是的 昨天
Yeah. Yesterday.

573
00:25:36,472 --> 00:25:37,972
晚上7:23
7:23 p.m.

574
00:25:37,974 --> 00:25:39,974
假设那支笔那时仍在海军部长的口袋里
And assuming that SECNAV still had the pen in her pocket--

575
00:25:39,976 --> 00:25:42,610
我交叉检查了她的时间表
I cross-referenced her schedule.

576
00:25:42,612 --> 00:25:46,480
Stalin下载时 Porter正和她十几岁的女儿在一个餐厅吃饭
Porter was at a restaurant having dinner with her teenage daughter when Stalin was downloading.

578
00:25:46,482 --> 00:25:48,181
他需要有多近
How close would he have to be?

579
00:25:48,183 --> 00:25:51,035
非常近 这是一支很小的笔 很短的天线
Close. It's a small pen-- small antenna.

580
00:25:51,037 --> 00:25:54,154
所以我检查了餐厅附近街道的监控录像
So I pulled street surveillance footage from near the restaurant,

581
00:25:54,156 --> 00:25:56,156
然后发现Stalin坐在他的车里
and found Stalin sitting in his car,

582
00:25:56,158 --> 00:25:58,075
正犯着叛国罪
committing high treason.

583
00:25:58,077 --> 00:26:00,494
我猜到处都有耳目确实挺有帮助
I guess having eyes and ears everywhere can be helpful.

584
00:26:00,496 --> 00:26:02,212
但是不要告诉Bishop我说过这话
But don't tell Bishop I said that.

585
00:26:02,214 --> 00:26:03,864
车牌
License plate.

586
00:26:03,866 --> 00:26:06,166
已经加到通缉令里了 Gibbs
Already added to the BOLO, Gibbs.

587
00:26:06,168 --> 00:26:07,801
我们找到这家伙的几率
Our chances of finding this guy

588
00:26:07,803 --> 00:26:09,003
突然加速剧增了
just skyrocketed.

589
00:26:09,005 --> 00:26:10,888
Abbs 非常出色
Abbs, that's really great work.

590
00:26:25,570 --> 00:26:28,489
节哀顺变
I'm sorry for your loss.

591
00:26:30,442 --> 00:26:34,161
被杀的那个探员 是你的朋友吗
The agent who was killed-- was he a friend of yours?

592
00:26:34,163 --> 00:26:37,164
更像是我的哥哥
More like an older brother.

593
00:26:47,542 --> 00:26:50,177
一切都还好吗
Everything okay?

594
00:26:50,179 --> 00:26:55,349
不能告诉家人我在做什么是很痛苦的
It's tough not being able to talk to my family about what I do.

596
00:26:56,918 --> 00:26:58,802
你应该看看 当我告诉我妈
You should've seen my mom when I told her

597
00:26:58,804 --> 00:27:00,688
我在俄克拉荷马州外工作时她的表情
I was taking a job outside of Oklahoma.

598
00:27:00,690 --> 00:27:01,922
那你为什么说了
Why did you?

599
00:27:01,924 --> 00:27:05,476
嗯 那就是妈妈和爸爸之间的区别
Mm. That's the difference between Mom and Dad.

601
00:27:05,478 --> 00:27:09,029
他的第一条规矩就是 舒适使人安逸
His first rule is: comfort makes for complicity.

602
00:27:09,031 --> 00:27:12,766
意为只有不断挑战自己才能成长
Means the only way to grow is by challenging yourself.

603
00:27:12,768 --> 00:27:15,319
的确 这有助于记住我们工作的原因
Well, it helps to remember why we do the job.

604
00:27:15,321 --> 00:27:18,238
让自己不断前进
Keeps us going.

605
00:27:20,709 --> 00:27:23,494
事实上 我该回NSA了
Actually, I should get back to NSA.

606
00:27:23,496 --> 00:27:25,946
嗯 你可没那么容易溜走
Mm. You're not getting off that easy.

607
00:27:25,948 --> 00:27:27,998
Gibbs也喜欢规矩 第45条
Gibbs likes rules, too. Number 45:

608
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:29,783
自己清理自己的烂摊子
always clean up your mess.

609
00:27:29,785 --> 00:27:31,952
-怎么清理 -这个嘛 首先
- How? - Well, for starters,

610
00:27:31,954 --> 00:27:34,254
Rudolph Stalin的通缉令有回应了
the BOLO came back on Rudolph Stalin.

611
00:27:34,256 --> 00:27:35,973
我们知道他在哪了
We know where he is.

612
00:27:37,125 --> 00:27:39,727
走吧 没时间浪费了
Come on. Time's a-wastin'.

613
00:27:53,241 --> 00:27:54,691
好的 谢谢
Okay, thanks.

614
00:27:54,693 --> 00:27:56,410
特区警署说Stalin的汽车
Metro PD says Stalin's car

615
00:27:56,412 --> 00:27:58,579
仍旧停在前面很远的地方
is still parked in a lot out front.

616
00:27:58,581 --> 00:27:59,947
他们不确定他在哪个放映厅
They're not sure which theater he's in,

617
00:27:59,949 --> 00:28:02,149
不过一共就两个厅 你们想要我去哪儿
but there are only two screens. Where do you want me?

618
00:28:02,151 --> 00:28:03,483
我在武器与外勤训练中成绩拔尖
I aced my weapons and field training.

619
00:28:03,485 --> 00:28:05,252
你有枪吗 Ado Annie 
【注：歌剧《俄克拉荷马人》里的一个人物】 
You got a gun, Ado Annie?

620
00:28:05,254 --> 00:28:07,755
我把它留在我的四轮马车上了  
I left it in my surrey with the fringe on top.

621
00:28:07,757 --> 00:28:10,007
别对我引用《俄克拉荷马人》
Don't quote <i>Oklahoma</i> to me.

622
00:28:11,459 --> 00:28:13,427
呆在车里
Stay in the car.

623
00:28:13,429 --> 00:28:14,595
没问题
You bet.

624
00:28:38,453 --> 00:28:39,653
他
Him.

625
00:28:39,655 --> 00:28:41,121
就是他
That's him!

626
00:28:43,291 --> 00:28:44,708
联邦探员
Federal agent!

627
00:28:49,048 --> 00:28:50,363
站住 站住 站住
Stop, stop, stop!

628
00:28:58,973 --> 00:29:01,141
Bishop 你为什么用车撞他
Bishop, why'd you hit him with the car?

629
00:29:01,143 --> 00:29:03,894
事实上 是他撞到车上的
Well... technically, he ran into the car.

630
00:29:03,896 --> 00:29:07,047
必须说 那是凭直觉的 直觉是好事 对吗
Got to say, that was a gut move. Gut's good, right?

631
00:29:07,049 --> 00:29:09,349
我们故意让这家伙跑出来的
We intentionally flushed the guy out.

632
00:29:09,351 --> 00:29:10,767
Gibbs一直都守在出口
Gibbs had the exit covered the whole time.

633
00:29:10,769 --> 00:29:11,985
什么
What?

634
00:29:12,854 --> 00:29:15,572
她在刚刚那一瞬间变成Palmer了 老大
She pulled a Palmer on this guy, boss.

635
00:29:18,393 --> 00:29:21,829
至少他会安静地和我们回去
At least he'll go quietly.

636
00:29:24,115 --> 00:29:26,500
除非有律师在 否则我什么都不会说
I'm not saying anything without a lawyer.

637
00:29:26,502 --> 00:29:28,452
你们用车撞了我
You hit me with a car.

638
00:29:28,454 --> 00:29:30,420
我以为他要逃跑
I thought he was getting away.

639
00:29:30,422 --> 00:29:33,907
我读了他的档案 他在高中时是个田径明星
I read in his file that he was a high school track star.

640
00:29:34,742 --> 00:29:37,410
我能够记得我读的几乎所有东西
I remember almost everything I read.

641
00:29:38,913 --> 00:29:42,466
其中包括很多审讯记录
Which includes more than a few interrogation transcripts.

642
00:29:42,468 --> 00:29:43,750
言外之意是
Meaning what?

643
00:29:43,752 --> 00:29:45,769
我有一个主意
I have an idea.

644
00:29:45,771 --> 00:29:48,105
等一下 这些
Hang on. These.

645
00:29:48,107 --> 00:29:49,189
什么
What?

646
00:29:49,191 --> 00:29:50,390
我需要借用这个
I need to borrow this.

647
00:29:50,392 --> 00:29:52,309
谢谢
Thank you.

648
00:29:52,311 --> 00:29:54,361
审讯最重要的原则就是
Now, a major principle of an interrogation

649
00:29:54,363 --> 00:29:56,363
让嫌疑人自己下结论 是吧
is to let the suspect draw their own conclusions, right?

650
00:29:56,365 --> 00:30:00,367
所以 只要我不说自己是他的律师
Which means, as long as I never <i>say</i> I'm his lawyer,

651
00:30:00,369 --> 00:30:03,370
他也不问的话...
as long as he never asks...

652
00:30:03,372 --> 00:30:04,872
站住
Stop.

653
00:30:08,793 --> 00:30:10,410
我能做到
I can keep up.

654
00:30:12,947 --> 00:30:16,216
在你撞到他之前 他看见你没有
Did that guy see you before you hit him?

655
00:30:16,218 --> 00:30:18,001
没有
Mm-mm.

656
00:30:20,939 --> 00:30:24,308
我们已经打电话给公共辩护处...
Look, we called the public defender...

657
00:30:24,310 --> 00:30:25,559
嗨 你...
Hey. What...

658
00:30:25,561 --> 00:30:26,727
终于来了 你是我的...
Finally. Are you my...?

659
00:30:26,729 --> 00:30:28,478
不好意思我穿成这样
Sorry for the outfit.

660
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:30,180
今天本该我休假的 我是Ellie Bishop
Today was supposed to be my day off. Ellie Bishop.

661
00:30:30,182 --> 00:30:31,265
你问过他问题吗
Have you been asking him questions?

662
00:30:31,267 --> 00:30:32,799
从法律上讲 我们有权
Legally, we can ask

663
00:30:32,801 --> 00:30:34,134
想问多少就问多少
as many questions as we want.

664
00:30:34,136 --> 00:30:36,770
由犯罪嫌疑人决定要不要在无律师的情况下开口
Up to the suspect to talk without a lawyer.

665
00:30:36,772 --> 00:30:38,305
说的没错 你想开口吗
That's true.Do you want to talk?

666
00:30:38,307 --> 00:30:42,409
我们是不是应该先私下谈谈 或者...
Shouldn't we speak somewhere in private first? Or...

667
00:30:42,411 --> 00:30:43,977
由你决定 我已经看过了相关文件
It's up to you. I mean, I've read the file,

668
00:30:43,979 --> 00:30:45,529
他们这个谋杀案的确证据确凿
and they do have a pretty solid murder case.

669
00:30:45,531 --> 00:30:48,198
-谋杀 -没错 一个联邦探员被杀
- Murder? - Yeah. Of a federal agent.

670
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:50,167
不可能 我 我没杀过人
No way. I-I didn't kill anybody.

671
00:30:50,169 --> 00:30:52,252
他们发现了海军部长钢笔上的蹊跷
They know about the pen on the Secretary of the Navy.

672
00:30:52,254 --> 00:30:54,171
他们查出你当时在餐馆
They know that you were at the restaurant,

673
00:30:54,173 --> 00:30:55,622
也知道了一千万美元的事
and they know about the $10 million.

674
00:30:55,624 --> 00:30:57,157
你可以坦白从宽的
You can help yourself, though.

675
00:30:57,159 --> 00:30:58,425
如果你认罪的话
If you cop to the murder,

676
00:30:58,427 --> 00:31:00,794
-也许可以减刑 -我没杀人
- might reduce sentencing. - I didn't kill anybody!

677
00:31:00,796 --> 00:31:02,796
你朝一个联邦探员的胸口连射三枪
You shot a federal agent three times in the chest!

678
00:31:02,798 --> 00:31:04,264
喂 别太激动
Hey! Take it down a peg.

679
00:31:04,266 --> 00:31:06,099
他说他没杀人 好吗
He said he didn't kill anybody, okay?

680
00:31:06,101 --> 00:31:08,268
-我们先听他把话说完 -那你让他快说
- Let's hear him out. - Then you make it fast.

681
00:31:08,270 --> 00:31:10,520
我没有勒索政府
I did not extort the government,

682
00:31:10,522 --> 00:31:13,056
我也没有杀这个探员
and I did not kill this agent.

683
00:31:13,058 --> 00:31:14,891
但我知道是谁做的
But I know who did.

684
00:31:14,893 --> 00:31:17,311
-名字 -Edward Gracy
- Name. - Edward Gracy.

685
00:31:17,313 --> 00:31:18,695
他之前卖过情报给我
He's sold me info before.

686
00:31:18,697 --> 00:31:20,364
一些技术机密之类的公司项目
Corporate stuff at tech secrets.

687
00:31:20,366 --> 00:31:22,849
这是他第一次提供政府情报
This is the first time he's offered government intel.

688
00:31:22,851 --> 00:31:24,117
所以你承认了叛国
So you're admitting to treason.

689
00:31:24,119 --> 00:31:25,569
我们该信他的话吗
We supposed to believe this?

690
00:31:25,571 --> 00:31:27,955
我不知道要不要相信他
I don't know if I believe him at all.

691
00:31:27,957 --> 00:31:30,123
需要他的地址来证明你说的话
Need an address to prove it.

692
00:31:40,585 --> 00:31:42,386
写吧
Here you go.

693
00:31:54,065 --> 00:31:55,047
我的控辩协议怎么办
Hey, what about my deal?

694
00:31:55,072 --> 00:31:56,734
这事你得跟你的律师商量
Oh, you'll have to take that up with your lawyer.

695
00:31:56,735 --> 00:31:57,985
你说过你是我的律师
You said you were my lawyer.

696
00:31:57,987 --> 00:32:00,220
不 我没说过 我给了你名片
No, I didn't. Gave you my card.

697
00:32:10,282 --> 00:32:11,999
这在法庭上能站得住脚吗
Is that gonna hold up in court?

698
00:32:12,001 --> 00:32:14,034
我不知道 我也不是律师
I don't know.I'm not a lawyer, either.

699
00:32:14,036 --> 00:32:17,537
好了 确认是城内一处办公室
All right, got confirmation on a downtown office,

700
00:32:17,539 --> 00:32:20,207
承租者名为Edward Gracy
rent in the name Edward Gracy.

701
00:32:20,209 --> 00:32:22,042
我已经通知了特区警署 他们严阵以待
I alerted Metro PD, and they're on standby.

702
00:32:22,044 --> 00:32:23,427
我正在适应这里的节奏
Getting used to your pace here.

703
00:32:23,429 --> 00:32:24,594
那你会需要这个的
Well, then you're gonna need this.

704
00:32:27,048 --> 00:32:30,767
呃...这东西之前有人穿过吗
Uh... h-has this been used?

705
00:32:33,422 --> 00:32:35,255
我是Bishop
Bishop.

706
00:32:36,974 --> 00:32:38,108
是的 长官
Yes, sir.

707
00:32:38,110 --> 00:32:39,643
当然
Of course.

708
00:32:40,528 --> 00:32:41,761
是...是的
Y... Yes.

709
00:32:41,763 --> 00:32:43,096
是的 马上
Yes, right away.

710
00:32:43,098 --> 00:32:44,648
出什么事了 特区警署出状况了
What's the matter? There a problem with Metro?

711
00:32:44,650 --> 00:32:46,400
不是 是我在NSA的上司
No. Uh, it was my boss at NSA.

712
00:32:46,402 --> 00:32:49,236
他们要我立刻回总部汇报
They need me back at HQ to debrief immediately.

713
00:32:49,238 --> 00:32:50,704
要出发了
Got to go.

714
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:30,624
联邦探员
Federal agents!

715
00:33:30,911 --> 00:33:33,380
Edward Gracy
Edward Gracy!

716
00:33:34,730 --> 00:33:36,264
没人在
Nobody's home.

717
00:33:36,265 --> 00:33:38,366
你怎么想 我们又被耍了么
What do you think? We being played again?

718
00:33:39,368 --> 00:33:41,618
检查一下桌子
Check the desk.

719
00:33:46,875 --> 00:33:49,126
没什么有用的 只有些垃圾邮件 
Nothing here but junk mail,

720
00:33:49,128 --> 00:33:51,245
GSM的过期杂志
back issues of <i>GSM.</i>

721
00:33:51,247 --> 00:33:54,381
都是寄到这儿给Edward Gracy的
They're all addressed here to Edward Gracy.

722
00:33:54,383 --> 00:33:56,584
噢
Oh.

723
00:33:59,054 --> 00:34:01,305
这就是我们的幕后弈者
This is our master chess player?

724
00:34:05,060 --> 00:34:08,312
老大 我查到点东西
Boss, I got something back here.

725
00:34:08,314 --> 00:34:11,765
这绝对是Gracy制造窃听器的地方
Well, this is definitely where Gracy makes his bugs,

726
00:34:11,767 --> 00:34:15,653
而且显然还提高对心脏疾病的关注率
and apparently raises awareness about heart disease, as well.

727
00:34:15,655 --> 00:34:16,770
慈善机构信函
Charity mailers?

728
00:34:16,772 --> 00:34:18,572
-难道凶手很有善心 -不
- Our killer has a conscience? - Nope.

729
00:34:18,574 --> 00:34:20,074
是他的目标有善心
His targets do.

730
00:34:20,076 --> 00:34:23,410
寄给海军部长Sarah Porter的邮递收据
Shipping receipt for a mailer sent to Sarah Porter.

731
00:34:23,412 --> 00:34:24,645
他把窃听器
SECNAV. He's sending the bugs

732
00:34:24,647 --> 00:34:25,863
和宣传单一起寄出
with the brochures.

733
00:34:25,865 --> 00:34:27,481
垃圾邮件 免费赠品
Junk mail free gifts.

734
00:34:27,483 --> 00:34:28,649
并非回邮地址标签
Instead of return-address labels,

735
00:34:28,651 --> 00:34:30,417
你得到一支超级间谍笔
you get a super spy pen?

736
00:34:30,419 --> 00:34:31,919
这可是很大风险 甚至无法保证
It's a big risk with no guarantee

737
00:34:31,921 --> 00:34:33,987
这支笔能够通过你的"废品匣" 更不用说进入MTAC了
it's gonna make it past your junk drawer, let alone MTAC.

738
00:34:33,989 --> 00:34:35,372
这儿全都是收据
This is full of receipts.

739
00:34:35,374 --> 00:34:36,841
他定时发送这些邮件
He sends them out like clockwork.

740
00:34:40,495 --> 00:34:42,847
都来自于相同的邮局
These are all from the same post office.

741
00:35:40,222 --> 00:35:41,572
喂
Hello.

742
00:35:41,574 --> 00:35:43,941
你在这儿做什么
What the hell are you doing here?

743
00:35:43,943 --> 00:35:46,243
呃...
Uh...

744
00:35:53,067 --> 00:35:55,502
我可以解释
Okay, I can explain.

745
00:35:55,504 --> 00:35:58,122
我深入调查Edward Gracy这个名字
I kept digging into the name Edward Gracy.

746
00:35:58,124 --> 00:35:59,873
我只是...我控制不住自己
I just...I couldn't help myself.

747
00:35:59,875 --> 00:36:01,709
回你的车上去
Get back in your car.

748
00:36:01,711 --> 00:36:03,961
好的 但等一下 Gracy这个名字是化名
Okay, but wait. Th-The name Gracy is an alias,

749
00:36:03,963 --> 00:36:06,463
我查到了一张仍在使用的信用卡 每周都有固定的消费
and I found an open credit card with weekly purchases...

750
00:36:06,465 --> 00:36:08,799
-Bishop -就是在这个邮局
- Bishop! - ...a-at this post office, okay?

751
00:36:08,801 --> 00:36:10,083
我是来这里
I-I came here

752
00:36:10,085 --> 00:36:11,185
追查线索的
to follow up.

753
00:36:11,187 --> 00:36:13,020
Gracy的邮箱就在这里面
Gracy's P.O. box is inside the store.

754
00:36:13,022 --> 00:36:14,855
我知道 他也在里面
I know! So is he.

755
00:36:14,857 --> 00:36:16,390
这是我一直想告诉你的
It's what I'm trying to tell you.

756
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,860
噢
Oh.

757
00:36:19,862 --> 00:36:22,429
你在监视他
You're on a stakeout.

758
00:36:24,783 --> 00:36:26,450
-老大 -Bishop
- Boss? - Bishop!

759
00:36:30,271 --> 00:36:31,104
快开车
Go!

760
00:36:49,758 --> 00:36:51,792
你在书里读到怎么让坏人缴械投降的吗
What, did you read a book on disarming bad guys?

761
00:36:51,794 --> 00:36:54,127
我有三个哥哥 别挣扎了
Three older brothers. Quit squirming!

762
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:55,429
我想我们会发现这把枪
I think we'll find this weapon's

763
00:36:55,431 --> 00:36:57,431
和谋杀Flynn的武器相符
a match to the one that killed Flynn.

764
00:36:58,817 --> 00:37:01,068
我来接手吧
I'll take it from here.

765
00:37:01,070 --> 00:37:02,186
-可以了么 -是的
- You got it? - Yeah.

766
00:37:02,188 --> 00:37:03,187
好的
All right.

767
00:37:03,189 --> 00:37:05,639
我们走吧 大块头
Here we go, big guy.

768
00:37:17,035 --> 00:37:18,752
怎么了
What?

769
00:37:20,422 --> 00:37:22,423
我们都是对的
We were both right.

770
00:37:22,425 --> 00:37:24,508
我们抓到了他
And we got him.

771
00:37:24,510 --> 00:37:27,511
你还是没看到重点 Bishop
You're still missing the point, Bishop.

772
00:37:36,471 --> 00:37:39,056
指纹显示这个人
Got a hit on the fingerprint.

773
00:37:39,058 --> 00:37:41,476
真名是Thaddeus Knox
Real name is Thaddeus Knox.

774
00:37:41,477 --> 00:37:43,677
因从事商业间谍活动受到多项指控
Multiple arrests for corporate espionage.

775
00:37:43,679 --> 00:37:45,479
现在又加上叛国罪和谋杀罪
Now we can add treason and murder.

776
00:37:45,481 --> 00:37:48,065
-这说不通啊 -又怎么了 Russell Crowe
【注：好莱坞男星 主演过角斗士】
- It doesn't make any sense. - What now, Russell Crowe?

777
00:37:48,067 --> 00:37:49,233
你的美丽心灵
【注：2001年出品的电影 讲述数学家John Nash的一生】
Hasn't your beautiful mind

778
00:37:49,235 --> 00:37:50,735
今天还没让你吃够苦头
gotten you in enough trouble today?

779
00:37:50,737 --> 00:37:52,954
找到答案前我是不会退出的
Look, I don't quit until I get it right, and our corporate

780
00:37:52,956 --> 00:37:54,822
我们这位开公司的花样美男并不符合测写
pretty boy just doesn't fit into the big picture.

781
00:37:54,824 --> 00:37:57,358
无论是NSA还是NCIS都没有见过他
We've never seen him--NSA or NCIS.

782
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:59,026
-他是个新手 -没错
- He's a first-timer. - Exactly.

783
00:37:59,028 --> 00:38:00,878
如果他一向把窃听器
But if he sends bugs to tech employees

784
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:04,382
寄给科技公司的雇员来窃取商业秘密的话 为什么突然把目标转向海军部长
looking for corporate secrets,why make the jump to SECNAV

785
00:38:04,384 --> 00:38:07,385
还冒着终身监禁的风险去杀人
and a crime that carries out a life sentence?

786
00:38:07,387 --> 00:38:08,869
有些事逼他离开了舒适圈
Something made him leave his comfort zone.

787
00:38:08,871 --> 00:38:11,705
这跟意识形态和权力无关 是...
It's not about ideology or power, it's...

788
00:38:11,707 --> 00:38:13,641
是自我挑战
it's about challenging himself,

789
00:38:13,643 --> 00:38:15,542
证明他能胜任这项工作
proving that he can do the job.

790
00:38:15,544 --> 00:38:16,594
他是为了讨谁的欢心呢
Who's he trying to impress?

791
00:38:16,596 --> 00:38:18,813
他的老板
His boss.

792
00:38:35,614 --> 00:38:36,774
对了 对了 对了 对了
Yup, yup, yup, yup.

793
00:38:40,502 --> 00:38:42,569
别告诉我 你能从这些杂乱无章的邮件中找到线索
Don't tell me those crazy papers are finally paying off.

794
00:38:44,573 --> 00:38:46,740
-Bishop -我有个
- Bishop... - I have staff lists

795
00:38:46,742 --> 00:38:48,759
今早在MTAC里的公司的人员名单
from the corporations in MTAC this morning.

796
00:38:48,761 --> 00:38:51,912
窃听器寄给了几乎所有公司的雇员 除了一家
Bugs have been sent to employees of every company except one.

797
00:38:51,914 --> 00:38:54,098
-就是给Gracy付钱的那个公司 -Beringer Marine
- The same company that's paying Gracy. - Beringer Marine.

798
00:38:54,100 --> 00:38:55,582
他们和海军部长有过节吗
What do they have against SECNAV?

799
00:39:03,359 --> 00:39:04,308
Gibbs探员
Agent Gibbs.

800
00:39:04,310 --> 00:39:06,593
你也是来听进展汇报的
You here for the update?

801
00:39:11,733 --> 00:39:13,651
怎么了
What's going on?

802
00:39:13,653 --> 00:39:14,986
我怎么知道
Hell if I know.

803
00:39:14,988 --> 00:39:17,071
部长女士让我停止工作
Madam Secretary's cut me out of the loop.

804
00:39:17,939 --> 00:39:20,441
是啊 就连我也注意到了
Yeah. I couldn't help but notice

805
00:39:20,443 --> 00:39:22,493
你们俩之间的紧张气氛
the tension between you two earlier.

806
00:39:22,495 --> 00:39:25,129
你知道 我不在乎接受命令
You know, I don't mind taking orders.

807
00:39:25,131 --> 00:39:29,616
但我更情愿它们来自海军陆战队成员
I'd prefer they come from fellow Marines,

808
00:39:29,618 --> 00:39:30,968
或者是服过兵役的人
or someone who's served.

809
00:39:30,970 --> 00:39:32,336
我明白
I hear you.

810
00:39:32,338 --> 00:39:34,505
一个平民发布影响数千名军官的命令
A civilian giving orders that affects thousands

811
00:39:34,507 --> 00:39:37,791
真是让我难以接受
of military personnel pisses me off more than you know.

812
00:39:37,793 --> 00:39:39,510
几个月前
Few months back,

813
00:39:39,512 --> 00:39:42,063
我还在海军部长候选人名单上
I was on the short list for the SECNAV appointment.

814
00:39:44,232 --> 00:39:46,684
我很荣幸 但我不觉得这是正确的
I was honored, but didn't feel right about it.

815
00:39:46,686 --> 00:39:48,602
为什么
Why?

816
00:39:48,604 --> 00:39:50,821
-你看起来资历不错 -也许吧
- You seem qualified. - Maybe.

817
00:39:50,823 --> 00:39:53,324
但我从没穿过制服
But I haven't served in uniform.

818
00:39:53,326 --> 00:39:55,526
而我对服过兵役的人充满敬意
And I have too much respect for those who have.

819
00:39:55,528 --> 00:39:56,810
比如你
Like you.

820
00:39:56,812 --> 00:39:58,195
Porter假装自己知道
It's not right

821
00:39:58,197 --> 00:40:00,481
这些军人到底需要什么 这很不对
for Porter to pretend she knows what they need.

822
00:40:00,483 --> 00:40:01,999
她本该做出正确选择 就像我一样
She should've done the right thing, like I did,

823
00:40:02,001 --> 00:40:03,334
拒绝这个任命
and declined the position.

824
00:40:03,336 --> 00:40:05,419
但是...
But...

825
00:40:05,421 --> 00:40:07,204
我猜她现在不得不退位了
I guess she'll have to now.

826
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:13,594
这是什么
What is this?

827
00:40:13,596 --> 00:40:15,546
NSA的窃听器
A bug at the NSA.

828
00:40:15,548 --> 00:40:16,681
谁能想到呢
Who would've thought?

829
00:40:16,683 --> 00:40:18,683
你背叛了我 陆战队员
You turn on me, Marine?

830
00:40:18,685 --> 00:40:20,685
唯一的背叛者是你 Ward
The only turncoat here is you, Ward.

831
00:40:20,687 --> 00:40:22,553
雇佣了一个商业间谍
By hiring one of your corporate spies

832
00:40:22,555 --> 00:40:25,139
来为难我 你置整个国家的安危于不顾
to embarrass me, you put the entire country at risk.

833
00:40:25,141 --> 00:40:26,941
我没做那种事
I had nothing to do with that.

834
00:40:26,943 --> 00:40:28,359
我只想保护这个国家
I only want to protect this country

835
00:40:28,361 --> 00:40:29,843
和为国效力的人民
and the people defending it.

836
00:40:31,063 --> 00:40:33,781
也许我没有服过役 但我明白
I may not have served,but I know about duty

837
00:40:33,783 --> 00:40:35,282
什么是职责和牺牲
and sacrifice.

838
00:40:36,451 --> 00:40:40,404
军装可不足以造就整只团队
Takes more than a uniform to make a team.

839
00:40:51,032 --> 00:40:53,417
Gibbs探员
Agent Gibbs?

840
00:40:53,419 --> 00:40:56,220
Tony和McGee说你还在这里
Tony and McGee said you'd still be here.

841
00:40:56,222 --> 00:40:58,055
是的
I am.

842
00:40:58,057 --> 00:41:01,592
抱歉 这么晚还打扰你
Sorry to...bother you so late.

843
00:41:01,594 --> 00:41:03,677
永远不要说抱歉
Never say you're sorry.

844
00:41:03,679 --> 00:41:05,846
这是脆弱的表现
It is a sign of weakness.

845
00:41:05,848 --> 00:41:09,483
我认为这是关键问题
I thought that was the point.

846
00:41:09,485 --> 00:41:12,770
尤其是今天过后
Especially after today.

847
00:41:12,772 --> 00:41:15,740
但我觉得我终于想通了一些东西
But I think I've finally figured something out.

848
00:41:15,742 --> 00:41:18,192
你总是得找到正确答案 是吧 Bishop
You always got to have the right answer, don't you, Bishop?

849
00:41:19,562 --> 00:41:22,246
很不幸 的确是的
Unfortunately.

850
00:41:22,248 --> 00:41:25,399
但如果你让我说完 我能解释这为什么是错的
But if you'll let me finish, I can explain why that's wrong.

851
00:41:31,706 --> 00:41:34,458
我努力工作
I work hard.

852
00:41:34,460 --> 00:41:38,045
当我跌倒时 我能立刻爬起来
And when I fall,I get right back up.

853
00:41:38,047 --> 00:41:41,081
我很聪明 而且我想做出改变
I'm smart, a-and I want to make a difference.

854
00:41:41,083 --> 00:41:46,053
我可以做到
And I can.

855
00:41:46,055 --> 00:41:50,474
我一直只顾着眼于整体的棋局
Been so busy looking at the...the chessboard on my own,

856
00:41:50,476 --> 00:41:53,811
却忘了我也是其中的一份子
I... I forgot to be a part of it.

857
00:41:55,697 --> 00:41:57,815
我没有表现出团队意识
I wasn't a team player.

858
00:41:59,050 --> 00:42:00,768
所以...
So...

859
00:42:00,770 --> 00:42:03,454
这就是我想说的
that-that's... that's what I wanted to say.

860
00:42:03,456 --> 00:42:04,738
就这些
That's it.

861
00:42:04,740 --> 00:42:06,240
晚安
Um, good night.

862
00:42:06,242 --> 00:42:07,992
好运
Or good... good luck.

863
00:42:07,994 --> 00:42:10,494
算了
Never mind.

864
00:42:10,496 --> 00:42:12,546
你忘了点儿东西
You forgot something.

865
00:42:17,919 --> 00:42:19,453
那不是我的
Uh, that's not mine.

866
00:42:19,455 --> 00:42:20,771
你的名字在上面
It's got your name on it.

867
00:42:31,233 --> 00:42:34,401
这是很多年前 我去NSA工作之前
This is my NCIS application from years ago.

868
00:42:36,137 --> 00:42:38,439
向NCIS提交的工作申请
Before I took the job at NSA.

869
00:42:38,441 --> 00:42:39,990
你怎么知道的
How did you know about this?

870
00:42:39,992 --> 00:42:42,409
你的名字有点熟悉 我回去查了查
Your name sounded familiar;I went back and looked it up.

871
00:42:42,411 --> 00:42:44,411
这就是你今天带上我的原因
That's why you brought me along today.

872
00:42:45,864 --> 00:42:47,147
你也在下一盘棋
You play chess, too.

873
00:42:49,034 --> 00:42:52,253
我想看看你是否还有能力应对挑战
I wanted to see if you were still up for a challenge.

874
00:42:52,255 --> 00:42:54,171
为什么
Why?

875
00:42:56,324 --> 00:42:58,876
我希望你留下
I'd like to keep you around.

876
00:42:58,878 --> 00:43:00,794
联合工作分配
Joint duty assignment.

